# CMake Conventions

## General
- Specify `cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.20)` or higher
- Use modern CMake: `target_*` commands over global `include_directories`/`add_definitions`
- Prefer imported/aliased targets over raw library names

## Zephyr Projects
- `find_package(Zephyr REQUIRED HINTS $ENV{ZEPHYR_BASE})` before `project()`
- Add sources with `target_sources(app PRIVATE ...)`
- For dual-image builds, embed remote firmware via `ExternalProject_Add` + `generate_inc_file_for_target`

## ESP-IDF Projects
- Include `$ENV{IDF_PATH}/tools/cmake/project.cmake` before `project()`
- Components use `idf_component_register()` — not raw `add_library`

## Style
- Use lowercase cmake commands (`add_library`, not `ADD_LIBRARY`)
- Quote all variable expansions in conditionals: `if("${VAR}" STREQUAL "value")`
- Group logically: options, dependencies, sources, target properties
